<mxfile host="app.diagrams.net">
  <diagram name="Page-1" id="SWiJgBnMTGN2MtllaUlM">
    <mxGraphModel dx="2054" dy="7737" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="4681" pageHeight="3300" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="oAKqMLOiMfUACglm2OSG-1" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1&gt;Initiative Charter&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2&gt;1. Executive Ask&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;John requested that Enterprise Architecture lead an effort with architecture and engineering to define where FIS has infrastructure standardization gaps and what needs to change from an infrastructure mandate perspective.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The ask is to assess current hosting and infrastructure practices, identify where environments are too bespoke or inconsistent, and recommend mandatory standards that improve automation, repeatability, operational control, and lifecycle readiness.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The expected outcome is a clear set of infrastructure mandates, enforcement points, exception handling, and a roadmap for adoption.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;2. Problem Statement&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Current infrastructure and hosting practices have varying levels of standardization across platforms, applications, environments, and operational teams. In some areas, server builds, software deployment, database configuration, monitoring, patching, security controls, and upgrade processes remain inconsistent or dependent on manual execution.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This creates several enterprise issues:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Increased operational risk&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Configuration drift across environments&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Slower infrastructure lifecycle management&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Higher effort for patching and upgrades&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Inconsistent security and monitoring posture&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Limited ability to automate deployments end-to-end&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Difficulty enforcing common infrastructure requirements&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Increased dependency on tribal knowledge and manual runbooks&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;The organization needs a clearer mandate for what must be standardized, automated, packaged, monitored, and governed across hosting platforms.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;3. Scope&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This initiative will assess current-state gaps and define future-state mandates across core hosting and infrastructure domains.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;In Scope&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Domain&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Scope Focus&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Hosting Platforms&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Standard hosting patterns, supported platforms, platform-specific requirements, and lifecycle expectations&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Server Builds&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Standard images, build automation, configuration baselines, naming, tagging, and CMDB registration&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Application Deployment&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Packaging, automated deployment, hands-off installation, rollback, and release repeatability&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Database Platforms&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;SQL Server and other database hosting patterns, configuration standards, patching, backup, and lifecycle requirements&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Security Controls&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Baseline hardening, access controls, secrets management, certificates, vulnerability remediation, and policy alignment&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Monitoring and Observability&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Required monitoring, alerting, logging, ownership metadata, and operational telemetry&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Patching and Upgrade Readiness&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;OS, middleware, database, and platform patching requirements, in-place upgrade readiness, and dependency management&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Automation&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provisioning, configuration management, deployment automation, compliance checks, and drift detection&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Operational Readiness&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Runbooks, support model, backup, recovery, monitoring, ownership, and handoff requirements&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Exception Handling&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Exception approval, risk ownership, expiration, remediation, and review process&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Out of Scope&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;The following are not the primary objective of this initiative:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Redesigning every hosting platform&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Selecting a new infrastructure platform without a separate decision process&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Replacing all existing engineering standards&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Creating detailed engineering implementation runbooks&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Performing application-by-application remediation planning&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Owning delivery execution for all remediation activities&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Resolving every platform-specific architecture debate in the first phase&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;This initiative defines the mandates, gaps, enforcement model, and roadmap. Engineering and platform teams will own detailed implementation plans where required.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;4. Business Drivers&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Driver&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Why It Matters&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Operational Consistency&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Standardized infrastructure reduces support complexity and improves reliability&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Automation&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Automated builds and deployments reduce manual effort, errors, and delays&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Lifecycle Management&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Standardized platforms and configurations improve patching, upgrades, and currency&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Security and Compliance&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Mandatory controls reduce inconsistent security posture and audit exposure&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Cost Control&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Fewer bespoke patterns reduce support overhead and platform fragmentation&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Resilience&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Standard backup, recovery, monitoring, and operational readiness improve service stability&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Speed to Delivery&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Repeatable patterns allow faster onboarding of applications and environments&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Reduced Technical Debt&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Mandates prevent continued growth of non-standard infrastructure patterns&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;h2&gt;5. Current-State Areas to Assess&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The assessment will document gaps, risks, and inconsistencies across the following areas:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Area&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Assessment Questions&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Compute / Server Builds&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are server builds standardized, automated, patched, tagged, monitored, and registered in CMDB?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Application Packaging&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are applications packaged and deployable without manual server installation steps?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Deployment Automation&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Can applications be deployed, upgraded, and rolled back through controlled automation?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Database Platforms&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are database platforms standardized for build, backup, patching, configuration, and monitoring?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Configuration Drift&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are environments consistent across dev, test, staging, production, and DR?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Security Baselines&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are hardening, IAM, secrets, certificates, firewall rules, and vulnerability controls consistently applied?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Monitoring / Observability&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are applications and infrastructure monitored using required enterprise tools and ownership metadata?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Patching&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are operating systems, middleware, runtime platforms, and databases patchable without excessive manual intervention?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Backup / Recovery&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are backup, restore, retention, and recovery requirements defined and validated?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;CMDB / Ownership&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are infrastructure components mapped to AppID, service owner, support owner, and operational contacts?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provisioning&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are environments created through approved provisioning workflows or manual processes?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Operational Readiness&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Are support model, runbooks, escalation paths, monitoring, and recovery procedures complete before production use?&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;h2&gt;6. Future-State Mandates to Define&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This initiative will define mandatory requirements in the following areas:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Mandate Area&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Required Direction&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Standard Hosting Patterns&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Applications must align to approved hosting patterns unless an exception is granted&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Automated Provisioning&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Infrastructure must be provisioned through approved automation or controlled provisioning workflows&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Standard Server Builds&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Server builds must use approved images, baselines, agents, security controls, and registration patterns&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Application Packaging&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Applications must be packaged for repeatable deployment and must not rely on manual server installs&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Deployment Automation&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Deployments must support automated install, upgrade, rollback, and validation where technically feasible&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Database Standardization&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Database platforms must follow approved build, backup, patching, monitoring, and configuration standards&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Monitoring and Alerting&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Required observability, logging, alerting, and ownership metadata must be in place before production use&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Security Baseline&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Security hardening, vulnerability management, secrets, certificate, and access control standards must be enforced&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Backup and Recovery&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Backup, restore, retention, and recovery validation must be defined for production workloads&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;CMDB / AppID Alignment&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Infrastructure must be associated with approved application, service, owner, and support metadata&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Operational Readiness&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Production readiness must be validated before go-live through architecture, engineering, and operations controls&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Exception Governance&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Exceptions must be time-bound, risk-owned, approved, documented, and remediated&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;h2&gt;7. Stakeholders&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Stakeholder / Group&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Role&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;John&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Executive requestor / leadership sponsor&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Enterprise Architecture&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Leads architecture record, mandate definition, scope control, and decision documentation&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Infrastructure Architecture&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provides platform standards, hosting requirements, and infrastructure design input&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Engineering Teams&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provides implementation input, feasibility assessment, current-state gaps, and remediation options&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Platform Operations&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provides operational readiness, supportability, monitoring, patching, and lifecycle requirements&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Security Architecture / Cyber&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provides security baseline, vulnerability, access, secrets, and compliance requirements&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Database Engineering&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provides database platform standards, patching, backup, HA/DR, and configuration requirements&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Observability / Monitoring Teams&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provides monitoring, logging, alerting, ownership, and operational telemetry requirements&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;CMDB / ServiceNow / AppID Owners&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provides asset registration, ownership, service mapping, and operational metadata requirements&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Application Owners&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provide application-specific constraints, deployment patterns, and remediation feasibility&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Governance / Review Boards&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Enforce standards through architecture review, operational readiness, exception, and funding processes&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;h2&gt;8. Expected Deliverables&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Deliverable&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Initiative Charter&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Defines ask, scope, drivers, stakeholders, and deliverables&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Current-State Gap Assessment&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Documents gaps across hosting, compute, database, security, monitoring, patching, automation, and operations&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Future-State Mandates&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Defines mandatory requirements for standardized hosting and infrastructure readiness&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Enforcement Model&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Defines where standards are checked and enforced across the delivery lifecycle&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Exception Model&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Defines approval, expiration, risk ownership, remediation ownership, and review cadence&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Roadmap&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Defines 0–30, 30–60, 60–90, and 90+ day path&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Executive Readout&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Provides a concise leadership summary for John&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Decision Log&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Captures decisions, open items, owners, and dates&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Action / Dependency Tracker&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Tracks actions, dependencies, owners, due dates, and spreadsheet linkage if needed&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;h2&gt;9. Timeline&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Timeframe&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Focus&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;0–30 Days&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Confirm scope, stakeholders, current-state domains, known pain points, and assessment structure&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;30–60 Days&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Complete current-state gap assessment and identify candidate mandates&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;60–90 Days&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Finalize future-state mandates, enforcement points, and exception model&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;90+ Days&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Establish roadmap, prioritize remediation, align governance processes, and begin adoption tracking&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;h2&gt;10. Decision / Approval Path&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Decisions should be captured in the Decision Log and escalated based on impact.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Decision Type&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Approval Path&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Architecture Standards&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Enterprise Architecture with input from infrastructure, platform, security, and engineering teams&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Platform-Specific Requirements&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Infrastructure Architecture and Engineering with Enterprise Architecture alignment&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Security Requirements&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Security Architecture / Cyber with Enterprise Architecture alignment&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Operational Readiness Requirements&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Platform Operations, SRE / Operations, and Enterprise Architecture&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Exception Approvals&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Defined exception approvers based on risk, platform, and business impact&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Executive Decisions&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Escalated to John or appropriate leadership when mandate adoption, funding, risk, or policy alignment is required&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;h2&gt;11. Governance Control&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This initiative must remain focused on defining infrastructure mandates, identifying gaps, and establishing enforcement and exception models.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The first governance control is scope discipline.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The effort should not become an open-ended debate over platform preferences, one-off application needs, or full infrastructure redesign. Those topics may be documented as dependencies or follow-on decisions, but they should not block definition of the enterprise mandate.&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="60" x="180" y="38" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
